I feel a hostile vibration.

611
00:41:39,787 --> 00:41:41,412
That'll be me. Sorry.

612
00:41:48,295 --> 00:41:49,789
Has he been that way long?

613
00:41:49,921 --> 00:41:52,839
Three hours.
It is the ultimate in concentration.

614
00:41:52,966 --> 00:41:54,709
Feels so good when you stop.

615
00:41:56,469 --> 00:41:59,007
I have no doubt
that in less than ten years,

616
00:41:59,138 --> 00:42:04,214
people everywhere will know that
only empathicalism can bring peace.

617
00:42:04,351 --> 00:42:07,850
Peace through understanding
is the only real...

618
00:42:08,938 --> 00:42:11,607
Well, hello. How are you?

619
00:42:11,733 --> 00:42:13,690
Just fine, thank you.
How are you?

620
00:42:13,818 --> 00:42:15,478
How long have you been in Paris?

621
00:42:15,611 --> 00:42:17,937
This is Mr Avery.
These are my friends.

622
00:42:18,073 --> 00:42:20,112
How do you do, boys?

623
00:42:20,241 --> 00:42:23,740
Would you mind if I had
my own conversation with this lady?

624
00:42:23,869 --> 00:42:27,036
- They don't understand English.
- You were talking English.

625
00:42:27,164 --> 00:42:30,912
It's hard to explain,
but it's all part of empathicalism.

626
00:42:31,042 --> 00:42:33,913
We don't have to communicate
with words.

627
00:42:34,045 --> 00:42:37,912
They understand me through the way
I feel, and the tone of my voice.

628
00:42:38,049 --> 00:42:41,583
- Sort of like a dog.
- Obviously, you don't understand.

629
00:42:41,719 --> 00:42:43,213
Who's buying the wine?

630
00:42:43,345 --> 00:42:45,752
- I am.
- I understand more than you think.

631
00:42:45,889 --> 00:42:49,423
- If you're saying that the wine...
- Let me show you something.

632
00:42:51,477 --> 00:42:55,309
Gentlemen, may I tell you
that you look like a mess of worms?

633
00:42:55,439 --> 00:42:59,271
And that you not only look like,
but you are, a mess of worms.

634
00:42:59,401 --> 00:43:01,808
I'll bet you've been here
all these years

635
00:43:01,945 --> 00:43:04,862
because if you left,
you'd be picked up for vagrancy.

636
00:43:04,989 --> 00:43:07,527
- Bravo.
- Your defence rests.

637
00:43:07,658 --> 00:43:09,781
This isn't funny.
You don't belong here.

638
00:43:09,910 --> 00:43:12,662
Neither do you,
which brings us to why I'm here.

639
00:43:12,788 --> 00:43:14,579
Monsieur, you dance with Mimi?

640
00:43:14,706 --> 00:43:17,162
No, thanks, I'm busy.
Didn't Gigi tell you?

641
00:43:17,292 --> 00:43:20,708
That's very rude,
refusing to dance with Mimi.

642
00:43:20,837 --> 00:43:23,754
Where I come from,
the man asks the girl to dance.

643
00:43:23,881 --> 00:43:25,921
You must come from the Stone Age.

644
00:43:26,050 --> 00:43:30,546
We think freely here. If a girl wants
to dance with a man, she asks him.

645
00:43:30,679 --> 00:43:34,213
We're not inhibited by
outmoded social conventions.

646
00:43:34,349 --> 00:43:37,848
I can see that.
Do you ask men to dance with you?

647
00:43:38,561 --> 00:43:40,185
Isn't it time you realised

648
00:43:40,313 --> 00:43:44,641
that dancing is nothing more than
a form of expression or release?

649
00:43:44,775 --> 00:43:48,060
There's no need to be formal
or cute about it.

650
00:43:48,195 --> 00:43:52,524
As a matter of fact, I rather feel
Iike expressing myself now.

651
00:43:52,657 --> 00:43:54,815
And I could certainly use a release.

652
00:47:31,938 --> 00:47:35,389
- Bonsoir. Vous étiez formidable.
- Merci.

653
00:47:35,525 --> 00:47:38,525
You certainly made friends
and influenced people.

654
00:47:38,652 --> 00:47:40,941
They're empathicalists.

655
00:47:41,071 --> 00:47:45,697
