745
00:57:03,954 --> 00:57:07,654
Take her, and whatever you do,
don't let her out of your sight.

746
00:57:08,499 --> 00:57:10,990
Do what I tell you.
Don't worry about it.

747
00:57:11,127 --> 00:57:15,290
Here, hold these balloons high
in the air, and when I say "run",

748
00:57:15,422 --> 00:57:18,755
run as fast as you can
and don't let the balloons go.

749
00:57:18,884 --> 00:57:21,505
Run as fast as I can
and don't let the balloons go.

750
00:57:21,678 --> 00:57:23,966
Right. Now, ready?

751
00:57:24,097 --> 00:57:27,097
Head up a little. You're so happy.

752
00:57:27,224 --> 00:57:28,802
Alright, run!

753
00:57:28,934 --> 00:57:30,132
Run!

754
00:57:30,269 --> 00:57:32,178
What? Oh, why did I ever...

755
00:57:32,854 --> 00:57:35,345
- What's wrong?
- I don't know which way to go.

756
00:57:35,482 --> 00:57:36,940
That way.

757
00:57:37,067 --> 00:57:40,186
I'm sorry, I'm nervous.
I've never done anything like this.

758
00:57:40,319 --> 00:57:44,186
There's nothing to be nervous about.
You're in Paris, the Tuileries.

759
00:57:44,323 --> 00:57:48,237
You've got balloons. There's
a sudden shower. You're very happy.

760
00:57:48,368 --> 00:57:51,073
- Why am I so happy?
- Because I say you are.

761
00:57:52,705 --> 00:57:55,825
That's all you have to know.
You're happy. Now, run!

762
00:57:57,084 --> 00:57:58,282
Great. That's great.

763
00:57:58,419 --> 00:57:59,617
Now, stop!

764
00:58:00,629 --> 00:58:01,827
Wonderful!

765
00:58:10,430 --> 00:58:12,387
Now, today you're not happy.

766
00:58:12,515 --> 00:58:15,006
- I'm hurt and...
- Right, a creature of tragedy.

767
00:58:15,142 --> 00:58:18,226
Heartbroken, suffering.
You're Anna Karenina.

768
00:58:18,770 --> 00:58:20,597
Shall I throw myself under the train?

769
00:58:20,731 --> 00:58:25,107
We'll see. For now, just wonderful,
noble self-sacrifice.

770
00:58:25,485 --> 00:58:27,940
Your lover
has just kissed you goodbye.

771
00:58:31,407 --> 00:58:34,194
You may never know that kiss again,
or love again.

772
00:58:34,326 --> 00:58:36,652
Marcel, put some tears in her eyes.

773
00:58:39,623 --> 00:58:41,415
There are tears in her eyes.

774
00:58:41,542 --> 00:58:44,377
Good. You're not only a model,
you're an actress.

775
00:58:44,503 --> 00:58:50,125
Jo, give me the works.
Heartbreak, longing, tragedy.

776
00:58:50,258 --> 00:58:51,882
Wet your lips.

777
00:58:52,760 --> 00:58:55,132
Good. Alright. Now, la steam!

778
00:58:55,262 --> 00:58:56,258
La steam!

779
00:58:56,388 --> 00:58:58,760
That's great. Just like the movie.

780
00:58:58,891 --> 00:59:00,764
Poor Anna Karenina.

781
00:59:00,892 --> 00:59:02,470
No, not too much steam.

782
00:59:02,602 --> 00:59:06,682
Cut down the steam.
That's wonderful. That's it.

783
00:59:09,775 --> 00:59:14,152
Good. Now give her some flowers.
Flowers. Arms full.

784
00:59:14,279 --> 00:59:17,280
Alright. More. More. More!

785
00:59:17,657 --> 00:59:20,230
Alright, Jo, it's spring.
You're in love.

786
00:59:20,368 --> 00:59:23,369
Now, turn around. Fabulous!

787
00:59:38,009 --> 00:59:40,167
You're walking out of the opera,

788
00:59:40,303 --> 00:59:43,256
Ieaving to the passionate
music of Tristan und Isolde.

789
00:59:43,389 --> 00:59:45,714
- You're very unhappy.
- What happened now?

790
00:59:45,849 --> 00:59:47,925
A rendezvous at the opera.
Two seats.

791
00:59:48,059 --> 00:59:50,052
He didn't show up. You're furious.

792
00:59:50,186 --> 00:59:54,515
When I say go, walk down with fire
in your eyes and murder on your mind.

793
00:59:54,649 --> 00:59:55,847
Wet your lips.

794
00:59:56,275 --> 01:00:00,107
You're Isolde. You're a queen.
Now, go, go, go!

795
01:00:01,363 --> 01:00:03,901
You're furious at Tristan.

796
01:00:04,032 --> 01:00:05,656
That's great.

797
01:00:19,379 --> 01:00:21,537
Today,
you're just a simple little girl.

798
01:00:21,673 --> 01:00:25,504
You live on the Seine, and you're
trying to catch a fish for lunch.

799
01:00:26,636 --> 01:00:29,672
Jo, fish. I want you
to look like you're fishing.

800
01:00:29,805 --> 01:00:32,592
I'm trying,
but I've never fished before.

801
01:00:32,724 --> 01:00:36,508
That's quite obvious. You might
just as well be flying a kite.

802
01:00:37,646 --> 01:00:39,603
Don't look like such an amateur.

803
01:00:39,773 --> 01:00:41,184
You're just not fishing.

804
01:00:41,316 --> 01:00:44,400
I am, but it's caught on something.

805
01:00:44,528 --> 01:00:46,899
Well, give it a yank.

806
01:00:47,030 --> 01:00:49,069
Pretend you caught a fish.
Pull it out.

807
01:00:50,575 --> 01:00:52,152
Marvellous!

808
01:00:55,788 --> 01:01:00,449
- Here's what I want you to be.
- I know. I'm a princess at a ball.

809
01:01:00,584 --> 01:01:04,830
The bird is Prince Charming,
turned into a bird by a sorcerer.

810
01:01:04,962 --> 01:01:07,536
But we've decided
not to let it spoil the ball

811
01:01:07,673 --> 01:01:10,674
and to go on dancing
as if nothing had happened.

812
01:01:10,801 --> 01:01:12,425
You've outgrown me.

813
01:01:13,512 --> 01:01:16,631
Alright. Now, give him a kiss.

814
01:01:17,098 --> 01:01:20,514
He's your Prince Charming, isn't he?
Well, get happy!

815
01:01:21,644 --> 01:01:23,055
That's a killer.

816
01:01:27,483 --> 01:01:29,890
Alright, Marcel, lights!

817
01:01:33,154 --> 01:01:36,025
Jo! Jo, where are you?

818
01:01:37,074 --> 01:01:39,779
Tell me when you're ready. Say "go".

819
01:01:39,910 --> 01:01:42,152
I'm ready. What are you gonna do?

820
01:01:42,287 --> 01:01:45,656
Never mind what I'm going to do.
Just say "go".

821
01:01:46,416 --> 01:01:47,744
Alright. Go!

822
01:01:51,254 --> 01:01:54,420
Holy Moses! You look fabulous!

823
01:01:54,548 --> 01:01:55,746
Look, stop.

824
01:01:56,550 --> 01:01:57,665
Stop!

825
01:01:57,801 --> 01:02:02,048
- I can't stop. Take the picture.
- Stop!

826
01:02:02,180 --> 01:02:06,094
I don't want to stop. I like it.
Take the picture.

827
01:02:26,911 --> 01:02:30,445
This is your wedding day,
the happiest day of your life.

828
01:02:30,581 --> 01:02:33,914
Bells are ringing, flowers blooming,
angels singing.

829
01:02:34,042 --> 01:02:38,538
The man you love more than anyone
is inside the church waiting for you.

830
01:02:39,840 --> 01:02:41,500
What's the matter?

831
01:02:42,300 --> 01:02:45,586
I just feel so dishonest
in this wedding dress.

832
01:02:45,720 --> 01:02:50,049
It's not the happiest day of my life.
No one's waiting for me anywhere.

833
01:02:50,182 --> 01:02:54,310
But you weren't Anna Karenina.
The bird wasn't Prince Charming.

834
01:02:54,436 --> 01:02:56,761
- Please, Dick.
- I don't understand.

835
01:02:56,897 --> 01:02:58,521
Yes, I know.

836
01:02:58,648 --> 01:03:01,104
Oh, mais quelle mariée charmante!

837
01:03:01,234 --> 01:03:04,685
On ne m'avait pas dit qu'il y aurait
un mariage aujourd'hui.

838
01:03:04,820 --> 01:03:05,935
Mais entrez donc.

839
01:03:06,072 --> 01:03:08,147
But, Padre, we're not here to marry.

840
01:03:08,282 --> 01:03:12,030
- Such a beautiful bride.
- This is not my dress.

841
01:03:12,160 --> 01:03:13,868
We're here to take pictures.

842
01:03:13,995 --> 01:03:18,040
Nous sommes ici pour photographie,
pour la magazine de la fashion.

843
01:03:18,166 --> 01:03:21,415
I'm sorry. Perhaps we should've
asked your permission first.

844
01:03:21,544 --> 01:03:24,544
No wedding? Quel dommage!

845
01:03:24,671 --> 01:03:26,213
Merci.

846
01:03:27,549 --> 01:03:28,545
Jo!

847
01:03:33,888 --> 01:03:35,465
Jo?

848
01:03:38,517 --> 01:03:41,850
I'm sorry. I don't know
what's the matter with me.

849
01:03:41,979 --> 01:03:45,561
Forget it and relax.
We've been working too hard.

850
01:03:45,690 --> 01:03:48,181
I suppose we'll be going home soon?

851
01:03:48,318 --> 01:03:50,191
That's it. You're homesick.

852
01:03:50,319 --> 01:03:54,364
Well, just this last picture,
then you'll be through.

853
01:03:54,490 --> 01:03:57,609
- And then what happens?
- We go home.

854
01:03:58,327 --> 01:03:59,358
And then?

855
01:04:00,203 --> 01:04:01,614
What do you mean?

856
01:04:01,746 --> 01:04:03,537
Will I see you any more?

857
01:04:03,665 --> 01:04:06,998
And how! If you model,
I can get you bookings.

858
01:04:07,126 --> 01:04:10,577
- We'd be working together every day.
- I'll model.

859
01:04:10,713 --> 01:04:12,670
Good. We'll put you to work.

860
01:04:12,798 --> 01:04:16,297
Stand here, please.
There's a good place. Fine.

861
01:04:19,762 --> 01:04:20,758
Lovely.

862
01:04:20,888 --> 01:04:23,842
Now, tip your head just a little bit.

863
01:04:24,850 --> 01:04:27,175
Good. A little smile.

864
01:04:29,980 --> 01:04:31,059
Jo.

865
01:04:33,108 --> 01:04:34,139
Yes?

866
01:04:35,068 --> 01:04:36,645
Something is wrong.

867
01:04:37,612 --> 01:04:39,319
No. Why?

868
01:04:39,447 --> 01:04:42,117
You're the saddest bride
I've ever seen.

869
01:04:42,242 --> 01:04:44,483
You look as if you've been jilted.

870
01:04:44,619 --> 01:04:46,695
This is your wedding day.

871
01:04:46,829 --> 01:04:50,778
The day you've dreamt of.
You're marrying the man you love.

872
01:04:50,916 --> 01:04:52,873
The man who loves you.

873
01:04:53,919 --> 01:04:55,117
He's the only...

874
01:04:56,213 --> 01:04:57,790
And you're...

875
01:05:06,555 --> 01:05:09,721
Dick, I thought
it would never happen.

876
01:05:11,226 --> 01:05:14,641
I never want to go home.
I love Paris!

877
01:05:14,771 --> 01:05:18,934
I love these clothes and
the little church. And I love you.

878
01:05:22,569 --> 01:05:24,609
What did you say?

879
01:05:24,738 --> 01:05:26,896
I love Paris.

880
01:05:27,032 --> 01:05:28,823
That's not what I heard.

881
01:05:31,619 --> 01:05:33,078
My, my, my...!

882
01:05:35,873 --> 01:05:37,664
Well, what do you know!

883
01:05:39,668 --> 01:05:41,127
¶ He loves

884
01:05:42,087 --> 01:05:43,878
¶ And she loves

885
01:05:44,839 --> 01:05:46,832
¶ And they love

886
01:05:47,383 --> 01:05:51,795
¶ So why can't... you love

887
01:05:52,179 --> 01:05:57,137
¶ And I love too?

888
01:05:59,853 --> 01:06:01,596
¶ Birds love

889
01:06:01,729 --> 01:06:03,852
¶ And bees love

890
01:06:04,774 --> 01:06:08,522
¶ And whispering trees love

891
01:06:09,445 --> 01:06:11,236
¶ And that's what

892
01:06:12,030 --> 01:06:15,862
¶ We both should do

893
01:06:19,745 --> 01:06:23,790
¶ I always knew someday

894
01:06:25,042 --> 01:06:27,829
¶ You'd come along

895
01:06:28,920 --> 01:06:32,668
¶ We'll make a twosome

896
01:06:33,549 --> 01:06:37,214
¶ That just can't go wrong

897
01:06:38,179 --> 01:06:40,218
¶ Darling

898
01:06:42,057 --> 01:06:43,885
¶ He loves

899
01:06:44,727 --> 01:06:46,518
¶ And she loves

900
01:06:46,645 --> 01:06:48,934
¶ And they love

901
01:06:49,064 --> 01:06:53,690
¶ So won't you love me

902
01:06:54,653 --> 01:07:01,271
¶ As I love you?

903
01:10:25,759 --> 01:10:28,214
Armande, let me see
a breeze in the trees.

904
01:10:28,344 --> 01:10:31,215
Not too much.
I don't want a cyclone.

905
01:10:31,347 --> 01:10:32,806
Fountains.

906
01:10:34,642 --> 01:10:37,595
It's thrilling!
It makes me cry for the Carolines.

907
01:10:37,728 --> 01:10:40,265
The correspondent from Pakistan
has accepted.

908
01:10:40,397 --> 01:10:43,433
The correspondent from Madrid
will be able to make it.

909
01:10:43,566 --> 01:10:46,602
And the man from Istanbul
will be at the presentation.

910
01:10:46,736 --> 01:10:48,694
Good. Now, where is Jo?

911
01:10:49,364 --> 01:10:50,443
Here she is.

912
01:10:50,573 --> 01:10:53,325
Thank heavens.
I thought you'd stand us up again.

913
01:10:53,451 --> 01:10:56,156
- How did the wedding pictures go?
- Wonderfully.

914
01:10:56,287 --> 01:10:58,160
He is a marvellous photographer.

915
01:10:58,289 --> 01:11:02,368
All you do is sit there.
I make my speech to the press,

916
01:11:02,501 --> 01:11:05,418
the curtains will open
and you dazzle 'em!

917
01:11:05,545 --> 01:11:07,870
- Give 'em the old pizzazz.
- I'll try.

918
01:11:08,006 --> 01:11:10,331
I will introduce you to them.

919
01:11:10,466 --> 01:11:12,755
Be charming
and answer their questions.

920
01:11:12,885 --> 01:11:16,301
- What sort of questions?
- It's remarkably simple.

921
01:11:16,430 --> 01:11:18,837
I've written editorials on it
for years.

922
01:11:18,974 --> 01:11:20,717
As one lady to another...

923
01:11:20,851 --> 01:11:23,472
We ought to look like
one lady to another.

924
01:11:23,603 --> 01:11:26,176
They'll want to know
who does your hair,

925
01:11:26,314 --> 01:11:29,231
what you eat, drink,
what sheets you sleep on.

926
01:11:29,358 --> 01:11:32,312
You're the authority
on how to be lovely.

927
01:11:32,444 --> 01:11:34,271
What am I going to tell them?

928
01:11:34,404 --> 01:11:36,527
Just listen and repeat after me.

929
01:11:37,365 --> 01:11:40,485
¶ On how to be lovely

930
01:11:40,618 --> 01:11:43,738
¶ You gotta be happy

931
01:11:43,871 --> 01:11:45,863
¶ When you can feel light and gay

932
01:11:45,998 --> 01:11:49,782
¶ Then you'll be lovely as a holiday

933
01:11:50,085 --> 01:11:53,002
¶ On how to be charming

934
01:11:53,213 --> 01:11:56,000
¶ You gotta be merry

935
01:11:56,132 --> 01:11:58,421
¶ If only to weave a spell

936
01:11:58,551 --> 01:12:03,212
¶ And you'll be
Iovely as a carousel, too

937
01:12:04,890 --> 01:12:07,760
¶ I know you can show how

938
01:12:07,893 --> 01:12:10,727
¶ It's all in the know-how

939
01:12:10,853 --> 01:12:13,890
¶ And once you know, oh how

940
01:12:14,023 --> 01:12:15,647
¶ The world looks good to you

941
01:12:15,775 --> 01:12:17,684
¶ As it should to you

942
01:12:18,360 --> 01:12:21,147
¶ On how to be lovely

943
01:12:21,279 --> 01:12:24,482
¶ You gotta be jolly

944
01:12:24,616 --> 01:12:26,276
¶ When you can be fancy-free

945
01:12:26,743 --> 01:12:31,203
¶ And flash a smile that folks
come flocking to see

946
01:12:33,666 --> 01:12:37,248
¶ You'll be as lovely as can be

947
01:13:07,447 --> 01:13:10,447
¶ Can't do it with make-up

948
01:13:10,574 --> 01:13:13,148
¶ You just gotta wake up

949
01:13:13,994 --> 01:13:16,366
¶ And starting to take up

950
01:13:16,830 --> 01:13:18,158
¶ The life delirious

951
01:13:18,582 --> 01:13:20,159
¶ Nothing serious

952
01:13:20,708 --> 01:13:23,911
¶ On how to be lovely

953
01:13:24,045 --> 01:13:26,666
¶ You gotta be cheery

954
01:13:26,797 --> 01:13:29,086
¶ I'll give you a guarantee

955
01:13:29,216 --> 01:13:31,007
¶ You don't need dough

956
01:13:31,134 --> 01:13:34,135
¶ You don't need a college degree

957
01:13:36,056 --> 01:13:39,424
¶ Make sorrow incidental

958
01:13:39,559 --> 01:13:42,096
¶ Let joy be monumental

959
01:13:42,228 --> 01:13:46,723
¶ And you'll be lovely

960
01:13:53,279 --> 01:13:56,778
¶ You'll be as lovely as can be

961
01:14:09,419 --> 01:14:11,494
Ah, beautiful!

962
01:14:12,672 --> 01:14:14,249
Beautiful!

963
01:14:14,381 --> 01:14:15,959
These are not my clothes.

964
01:14:16,091 --> 01:14:19,709
They were lent for tonight.
I'm being presented to the press.

965
01:14:19,845 --> 01:14:22,845
Alors! Your picture will be
in all the newspapers?

966
01:14:22,972 --> 01:14:23,968
Oh, yes.

967
01:14:24,098 --> 01:14:27,134
And they'll ask me
all sorts of questions.

968
01:14:27,268 --> 01:14:28,382
Oh!

969
01:14:28,519 --> 01:14:32,599
I think perhaps you had better stay
here with me, huh?

970
01:14:33,649 --> 01:14:34,644
Hello!

971
01:14:37,068 --> 01:14:39,524
Don't you remember me?
Jo Stockton?

972
01:14:39,654 --> 01:14:40,982
C'est Jo!

973
01:14:41,114 --> 01:14:44,482
On vous a manqué, mais on n'a pas
le temps de s'arrêter maintenant.

974
01:14:44,617 --> 01:14:47,487
Flostre part au café
et on est déjà en retard. Au revoir.

975
01:14:47,619 --> 01:14:50,620
What were they saying about Flostre?

976
01:14:50,747 --> 01:14:54,959
That he is speaking at the café
and that they are late.

977
01:15:08,139 --> 01:15:10,380
Mr Avery will be by in five minutes.

978
01:15:10,516 --> 01:15:13,007
Ask him to pick me up at the café.

979
01:15:19,774 --> 01:15:21,482
Vous retrouverez tout cela

980
01:15:21,609 --> 01:15:23,317
à travers tous mes écrits
sur I'empathicalisme.

981
01:15:23,444 --> 01:15:26,361
La spiritualité
inhérente à I'empathicalisme

982
01:15:26,488 --> 01:15:30,652
matérialise les plus nobles aspects
de la nature humaine.

983
01:15:30,784 --> 01:15:32,741
Consciemment ou inconsciemment,

984
01:15:32,869 --> 01:15:35,739
elle est perceptible
dans tout ce qui nous touche.

985
01:15:35,872 --> 01:15:40,414
Dans nos meilleures sculptures...
Et dans notre meilleure littérature.

986
01:15:49,801 --> 01:15:51,176
Pardon, monsieur.

987
01:15:51,302 --> 01:15:54,173
Je suis... terribly sorry.

988
01:15:54,305 --> 01:15:56,878
- I...
- Quite alright, mademoiselle.

989
01:15:57,016 --> 01:15:58,214
You're quite welcome.

990
01:16:01,853 --> 01:16:05,518
Etudiez la statue un instant.
Je reviens tout de suite.

991
01:16:09,235 --> 01:16:10,812
Now, mademoiselle.

992
01:16:10,945 --> 01:16:13,945
I can't believe it.
I thought you'd be old.

993
01:16:14,073 --> 01:16:16,777
Well, I mean, a philosopher
and professor.

994
01:16:16,908 --> 01:16:19,909
It all suggests age.
I mean, maturity.

995
01:16:20,036 --> 01:16:22,029
