1232
01:30:59,036 --> 01:31:01,408
Professor, they want to make
a fool of you.

1233
01:31:01,538 --> 01:31:04,373
- Are you making a fool of him?
- Me?

1234
01:31:04,499 --> 01:31:08,248
You're making things difficult.
You don't own empathicalism.

1235
01:31:08,378 --> 01:31:10,502
It's in the public domain.

1236
01:31:10,631 --> 01:31:14,213
- Why don't you trust these people?
- Because I know them well.

1237
01:31:14,342 --> 01:31:17,343
I know what they're here for
and it is not guidance.

1238
01:31:17,470 --> 01:31:19,759
Don't listen to her, Master. She is but a child.

1239
01:31:19,889 --> 01:31:21,798
They came to see me, not you.

1240
01:31:21,933 --> 01:31:24,767
To get me over to Duval's
to model their collection.

1241
01:31:26,478 --> 01:31:29,894
- I should have known.
- You should've heard what he said.

1242
01:31:30,023 --> 01:31:33,973
If we'd come a few minutes later,
you'd have found out for yourself.

1243
01:31:34,110 --> 01:31:35,770
You've said enough, Mr Avery.

1244
01:31:35,903 --> 01:31:38,939
Not yet. I haven't told you
what a phoney you are.

1245
01:31:39,073 --> 01:31:42,691
- Get out of my house.
- I'm not ready to leave.

1246
01:31:42,826 --> 01:31:45,068
I think I can change your mind.

1247
01:31:45,203 --> 01:31:47,777
Catch!

1248
01:31:47,914 --> 01:31:49,705
Oh! Oh, no!

1249
01:31:50,541 --> 01:31:54,290
Look what you've done!
Bursting in here like a hoodlum.

1250
01:31:54,420 --> 01:31:56,745
- I never touched him.
- Go away!

1251
01:31:56,880 --> 01:31:59,667
It's time you woke up
to your responsibilities.

1252
01:31:59,800 --> 01:32:01,543
Will you please leave?

1253
01:32:01,676 --> 01:32:04,677
Duval can't show his collection
without you.

1254
01:32:04,804 --> 01:32:07,377
You can't do this to him,
or to all the others.

1255
01:32:07,515 --> 01:32:08,629
Hundreds of people.

1256
01:32:08,849 --> 01:32:11,008
I'm not interested in your people.

1257
01:32:11,143 --> 01:32:15,603
- Your empathy is a little one-sided.
- Get out!

1258
01:32:15,731 --> 01:32:16,810
Alright!

1259
01:32:17,691 --> 01:32:19,517
I assume you mean me, too.

1260
01:32:20,318 --> 01:32:22,524
On you it looks cute, sugar.

1261
01:32:27,741 --> 01:32:29,781
Well, you fixed everything!

1262
01:32:29,910 --> 01:32:33,907
If you can't lick 'em, join 'em
and if you can't join 'em, lick 'em!

1263
01:32:34,039 --> 01:32:36,529
- Tell Duval I'm sorry.
- Where are you going?

1264
01:32:36,666 --> 01:32:40,200
There's a plane to New York
at 10:30 p.m. and I'm on it.

1265
01:32:41,045 --> 01:32:43,915
You can't do this to me! Come back!

1266
01:32:44,048 --> 01:32:48,590
How dare you leave me in the street
Iike this! Taxi!

1267
01:32:59,561 --> 01:33:02,515
- Have they gone?
- They've gone.

1268
01:33:02,648 --> 01:33:05,897
- And you're still here?
- I'm still here.

1269
01:33:06,026 --> 01:33:07,982
Are you alright?

1270
01:33:08,111 --> 01:33:09,273
Well.

1271
01:33:09,987 --> 01:33:13,653
In fact, I feel wonderful.

1272
01:33:15,035 --> 01:33:17,442
I can't tell you how sorry I am.

1273
01:33:17,579 --> 01:33:21,907
I had no idea they were coming,
or what got into Dick.

1274
01:33:22,041 --> 01:33:27,117
My dear, you mustn't assume guilt
for something that was unavoidable.

1275
01:33:28,171 --> 01:33:29,879
They've gone.

1276
01:33:31,091 --> 01:33:35,088
You are here.
That's all that matters now.

1277
01:33:35,219 --> 01:33:38,090
Nice of you to say so,
but it was me...

1278
01:33:38,222 --> 01:33:40,926
You have the most penetrating eyes.

1279
01:33:41,058 --> 01:33:43,727
I can still see them
when I close mine.

1280
01:33:43,852 --> 01:33:45,643
- Professor?
- Call me Émile.

1281
01:33:45,770 --> 01:33:48,937
Would there be any value
in my contacting philosophers

1282
01:33:49,065 --> 01:33:52,231
in cities like
Omaha and Detroit and...

1283
01:33:52,360 --> 01:33:55,064
and acquainting them
with empathicalism?

1284
01:33:55,195 --> 01:33:58,564
Your mouth suggests to me
burgundy velvet.

1285
01:33:58,699 --> 01:34:03,609
Dr Post, who runs a shop I worked in,
has contacts in several universities.

1286
01:34:03,745 --> 01:34:05,536
Please.

1287
01:34:08,290 --> 01:34:10,117
Don't say another word.

1288
01:34:10,251 --> 01:34:13,335
- But I came here to talk.
- We'll talk.

1289
01:34:13,462 --> 01:34:16,830
- Later.
- Why don't I come back later?

1290
01:34:16,965 --> 01:34:18,423
But I need you now.

1291
01:34:19,217 --> 01:34:22,632
Professor Flostre, I came to talk
with a philosopher.

1292
01:34:22,762 --> 01:34:25,335
You're talking like a man.

1293
01:34:25,472 --> 01:34:28,592
But I am a man. And you're a woman.

1294
01:34:28,767 --> 01:34:31,174
That's not what I came
to talk about.

1295
01:34:31,311 --> 01:34:32,770
My dear.

1296
01:34:35,773 --> 01:34:38,857
There is a magical moment
waiting for us.

1297
01:34:38,984 --> 01:34:42,934
- Don't come any closer.
- Why are you behaving like this?

1298
01:34:43,071 --> 01:34:47,780
- You come from Greenwich Village.
- I'm moving uptown. Yonkers.

1299
01:34:47,909 --> 01:34:49,533
But before you move...

1300
01:35:03,465 --> 01:35:07,082
I cannot keep them waiting.
I must make an announcement.

1301
01:35:07,218 --> 01:35:10,717
- What shall I say?
- Tell them it was all my fault.

1302
01:35:22,733 --> 01:35:24,476
Maggie, where's Dick?

1303
01:35:24,610 --> 01:35:28,274
You told him to go and he went.
He flies at 10:30 p.m.

1304
01:35:28,405 --> 01:35:29,567
He mustn't!

1305
01:35:29,697 --> 01:35:31,904
I knew you would not let us down!

1306
01:35:32,033 --> 01:35:35,651
- You must do the collection!
- Later. I've got to get to Dick.

1307
01:35:35,786 --> 01:35:38,703
- We are so late already.
- I want to help.

1308
01:35:38,831 --> 01:35:42,116
I know how you feel,
even if you think I don't.

1309
01:35:42,250 --> 01:35:46,912
- I can put myself in your place.
- Maggie, that's empathy!

1310
01:35:47,046 --> 01:35:50,497
That's what you've been talking
about! Why didn't you say?

1311
01:35:50,633 --> 01:35:53,918
Get to work. I'll take care
of Dick. Leave it to me!

1312
01:35:54,053 --> 01:35:56,970
Lettie, what is the name
of Dick Avery's hotel?

1313
01:35:57,097 --> 01:35:59,848
- Le Savoyard.
- Get me the number.

1314
01:35:59,974 --> 01:36:03,177
- How long before we can begin?
- We're ready.

1315
01:36:05,646 --> 01:36:07,306
Messieurs et mesdames.

1316
01:36:07,439 --> 01:36:10,974
We are proud to bring you
a new collection by Paul Duval,

1317
01:36:11,109 --> 01:36:13,149
inspired by the Quality Woman,

1318
01:36:13,278 --> 01:36:17,738
chosen to represent a great American
fashion magazine, Quality.

1319
01:36:17,865 --> 01:36:20,072
We begin with Hors d'Oeuvre.

1320
01:36:33,588 --> 01:36:36,873
Hotel Savoyard?
M. Dick Avery, s'il vous plaît?

1321
01:36:43,764 --> 01:36:48,674
- Monsieur, your bill is ready.
- I know. 352,428 francs.

1322
01:36:48,810 --> 01:36:51,810
- Merci, monsieur. Come back soon.
- Thank you.

1323
01:36:52,980 --> 01:36:56,847
He doesn't answer, madame.
I will give you the desk.

1324
01:36:58,735 --> 01:37:02,779
Hello. Monsieur Avery?
He just left.

1325
01:37:02,906 --> 01:37:05,443
Well, run out and get him!
It's urgent!

1326
01:37:06,242 --> 01:37:07,440
Oui, madame.

1327
01:37:10,621 --> 01:37:12,946
I'm so sorry. It was too late.

1328
01:37:27,762 --> 01:37:31,759
- Did you get him?
- No. We'll get him at the airport.

1329
01:37:31,891 --> 01:37:34,464
- I can't find it!
- How are you spelling it?

1330
01:37:34,602 --> 01:37:37,175
- A-U-L-Y.
- Orly. O-R-L-Y.

1331
01:37:37,312 --> 01:37:39,803
- You were there!
- I'm just so nervous.

1332
01:37:39,940 --> 01:37:41,932
- Are you ready?
- Just about.

1333
01:37:42,067 --> 01:37:44,736
Monsieurs et mesdames, Jonquille.

1334
01:37:44,861 --> 01:37:45,940
I'm ready.

1335
01:37:52,534 --> 01:37:55,784
You can board your plane now,
monsieur. Pleasant flight.

1336
01:37:55,912 --> 01:37:56,943
Thanks.

1337
01:38:01,292 --> 01:38:03,331
Attention! Attention!

1338
01:38:03,461 --> 01:38:07,244
Monsieur Avery?
Monsieur Richard Avery?

1339
01:38:07,381 --> 01:38:09,338
Maggie, is there any news?

1340
01:38:09,466 --> 01:38:13,594
They promised they'd get my message
to him before he boarded.

1341
01:38:15,888 --> 01:38:17,133
It's too late.

1342
01:38:17,265 --> 01:38:21,344
The clock must be fast.
He just hasn't got the message yet.

1343
01:38:31,277 --> 01:38:34,860
I'm sure he got it.
He didn't want to talk to me.

1344
01:38:37,533 --> 01:38:40,070
I don't blame him.
I hurt him too much.

1345
01:38:47,000 --> 01:38:51,542
And now, the finale
of the collection. Wedding Day.

1346
01:39:03,139 --> 01:39:05,013
What a beautiful bride!

1347
01:39:05,141 --> 01:39:07,180
Yes. Pity it isn't her wedding.

1348
01:39:25,201 --> 01:39:26,446
Professor!

1349
01:39:26,578 --> 01:39:28,404
Keep away from me, you!

1350
01:39:28,538 --> 01:39:31,953
If you lay one finger on me,
I will call your embassy.

1351
01:39:32,082 --> 01:39:35,700
I want to apologise.
She wasn't worth fighting about.

1352
01:39:35,836 --> 01:39:38,587
- Don't tell me I did that!
- You?

1353
01:39:38,713 --> 01:39:41,121
You didn't even give me a headache.

1354
01:39:41,257 --> 01:39:44,957
She did this to me, with a statue
that cost 200,000 francs.

1355
01:39:45,094 --> 01:39:48,545
- She did that?
- I have 18 stitches in my head.

1356
01:39:48,681 --> 01:39:51,254
- She gave you 18 stitches?
- And a gashed lip.

1357
01:39:51,391 --> 01:39:53,051
And six stitches in my ear.

1358
01:39:53,185 --> 01:39:56,304
Professor, I love every broken bone
in your body!

1359
01:40:01,776 --> 01:40:04,527
Excuse me, Duval. Where is Jo?

1360
01:40:04,653 --> 01:40:07,322
She was magnificent!
You should've seen her!

1361
01:40:07,447 --> 01:40:10,365
- Where is she?
- I don't know, she was here...

1362
01:40:10,492 --> 01:40:12,568
Lettie! Have you seen Jo?

1363
01:40:12,702 --> 01:40:15,619
No, I...
Oh, Dick, she was just great!

1364
01:40:15,746 --> 01:40:18,154
Maggie, where's Jo?
Have you seen her?

1365
01:40:18,290 --> 01:40:20,366
She was here, but she's disappeared.

1366
01:40:20,501 --> 01:40:23,335
- Did she say where she was going?
- I understand now.

1367
01:40:23,462 --> 01:40:26,628
She put herself in your place,
so put yourself in her place.

1368
01:40:26,756 --> 01:40:29,164
You'll meet each other
in somebody's place.

1369
01:40:29,300 --> 01:40:32,217
That's it!
Maggie, you ought to be president.

1370
01:40:32,345 --> 01:40:33,755
I thought I was!

